 a more\nefficient sputtering could better reproduce the observations. In conclusion,\nthe sputtering of ices by cosmic-rays collisions may be the most efficient\ndesorption mechanism at high density (a few $10^4$~cm$^{-3}$ under the\nconditions studied here) in cold cores, whereas chemical desorption is still\nrequired at smaller densities. Additional works are needed on both mechanisms\nto assess their efficiency with respect to the main ice composition.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Jun 2021 08:28:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-11"}
